    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Ti</abbr><ex>berius</ex></expan> Claudius Ca</supplied>isar A<supplied reason="lost">ugustus Germ</supplied>anic<supplied reason="lost">us <expan><abbr>pontif</abbr><ex>ex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">tribunicia potes</supplied>tate X<supplied reason="lost">IV<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <expan><abbr>imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> XXVII<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <expan><abbr>co</abbr><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan></supplied> V p<supplied reason="lost">ater patriai</supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">aedem</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>ncend<supplied reason="lost">io consumptam<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> a solo</supplied> de sua pe<supplied reason="lost">cunia restituit</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Zwei nicht aneinanderpassende Fragmente eines Epistyls erhalten. Maße von Fragment a): s.o.; Maße von Fragment b): -52.5 x 47.5 x 56. Ergänzungen nach G. Alföldy und S. Panciera. Alternativer Ergänzungsvorschlag: [Ti(berius) Claudius Drusi f(ilius) Ca]isar A[ugustus Germ]anic[us pontifex maximus] / [tribunicia potes]tate X[IV? imp(erator) XXVII? co(n)s(ul)] V p[ater patriai] / [aedem? 3 i]ncend[io consumptam? a solo] de sua pe[cunia restituendam curavit]</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography">
                <listBibl><bibl>CIL 06, 40417; fig α u. β; γ (Zeichnungen).</bibl><bibl>AE 1996, 0248.</bibl><bibl>S. Panciera, in: C. Panella (Hrsg.), Meta Sudans 1. Un'area sacra in Palatio e la valle del Colosseo prima e dopo Nerone (Roma 1996) 133-137; fig. 127 a u. b; fig. 128 (Zeichnung). - AE 1996.</bibl><bibl/></listBibl>
